From 35e41291922fbfdd2fe40c473dc377e5d4b6527d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marcus Figueiredo <figueiredo@protonmail.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 19:58:55 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] gpu: complete Android boot with gfxstream/ASG Vulkan on
 libkrun/HVF macOS

First full Android boot (sys.boot_completed=1) over libkrun/HVF on macOS
with hardware-accelerated Vulkan via gfxstream (ranchu/ASG). The ranchu
path failed in layers; each fix unblocked the next, traced via GPU worker
instrumentation, ANR backtraces, and host panics.

virtio_gpu.rs:
- new_gfxstream: plumb the real map_sender instead of a channel whose
  receiver was dropped. After the gfxstream blob map_ptr was populated,
  resource_map_blob reaches WorkerMessage::GpuAddMapping (hv_vm_map); the
  dead stub channel made send().unwrap() panic the GPU worker, hanging the
  guest's DRM_IOCTL_VIRTGPU_WAIT during ASG ring setup.
- transfer_read: implement by delegating to rutabaga.transfer_read instead
  of panicking; gfxstream's ASG ring issues TRANSFER_FROM_HOST_3D to read
  host-produced ring data back.

worker.rs:
- pass map_sender into new_gfxstream; drop temporary command-trace logging.

capy/main.rs:
- add androidboot.vsock_lights_port=6800. The cuttlefish lights HAL binds
  an AF_VSOCK listener on this port; absent the property it binds port 0,
  fails with EACCES and panics, leaving the VINTF-declared ILights service
  unregistered. system_server then blocks in waitForDeclaredService until
  Watchdog kills it, crash-looping zygote and blocking boot_completed.

Builds on the already-committed gfxstream map_ptr mmap fix (rutabaga
gfxstream create_blob) and createBlob error propagation.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
